    An ISCSI volume attachment.
    Note: This model distinguishes fields that are null because they are unset from fields that are explicitly set to null. This is done in the setter methods of the IScsiVolumeAttachment.Builder, which maintain a set of all explicitly set fields called __explicitlySet__. The hashCode() and equals(Object) methods are implemented to take __explicitlySet__ into account. The constructor, on the other hand, does not set __explicitlySet__ (since the constructor cannot distinguish explicit null from unset null). As a consequence, objects should always be created or deserialized using the IScsiVolumeAttachment.Builder.
